landingPage.name: TNG Testing Landing Page
landingPage.description: This landing page designed for the TNG Testing Community.
landingPage.content:
Welcome to the GDHCN Conformance Test Bed

This is a service provided by the World Health Organization (WHO), utilizing the Interoperability Test Bed (ITB) developed by EC DIGIT, to support conformance testing within the Global Digital Health Certification Network (GDHCN).

The GDHCN is a WHO-facilitated trust network that enables the cross-border verification of digital health documents, such as vaccination certificates and international patient summaries. It supports countries in building secure, interoperable digital public health infrastructure while maintaining full national control over data and systems.

This Test Bed allows implementers to validate their systems against GDHCN technical specifications, ensuring consistency and interoperability across jurisdictions.

For technical specification on the GDHCN, please visit: https://smart.who.int/trust/

landingPage.name: TNG Testing Landing Page for Community Admins
landingPage.description: This landing page designed for the TNG Testing Community Administrators.
landingPage.content:
Welcome to the TNG Testing Community!

As Administrator of this community you are able to change the settings and parameters for the whole community, but are most importantly responsible for test management within TNG TC (Trust Network Gateway Testing Community).

The test cases for implementation can be found here: WHO HAJJ Test Cases (GitHub)

The progress is tracked here in Jira: GDHCN Testbed Epic (Jira)

Onboarding and tutorials for new and old users here: Interoperability Test Bed Guides
